Chinese vs German Suspension Technology #shorts #technology #ytshorts

In this incredible suspension test, we witness a side-by-side comparison of suspension technology from China and Germany. Three vehicles — a BMW, an Audi, and the Chinese-made NIO ET9 — are driven over a stretch of speed breakers to evaluate their suspension response.

While the BMW and Audi visibly bounce and wobble over each bump, the NIO ET9 glides smoothly, showing no visible movement inside the cabin. This highlights the advanced active suspension system in the ET9, which adapts in real-time to road conditions, absorbing shocks before they reach the passengers.

China’s NIO is proving to be a serious player in automotive innovation, especially in comfort and tech. This test is a great showcase of how next-gen suspension systems are redefining ride quality.
